-- Portugal’s Trade Gap Narrows as Exports Increase, Imports Drop
-- B y   J o a o   L i m a
-- 2012-06-11T10:39:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-11/portugal-s-trade-gap-narrows-as-exports-increase-imports-drop.html
Portugal ’s  trade deficit  narrowed in
the three months through April as exports rose and imports
decreased, the country’s statistics institute said.  The trade deficit narrowed to 2.54 billion euros ($3.2
billion) from 4.59 billion euros in the same period a year
earlier, the Lisbon-based institute said today in an e-mailed
report. Exports rose 8.4 percent and imports fell 7.7 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Joao Lima in Lisbon at 
